# Cursor Rules — minecraft_playbook

## Project

LEGO-style Minecraft building manual for Japanese kids. Next.js 16 + React 19 + TypeScript.
Main data file: `lego-manual/app/data/volumes.ts`

## Rules

- All user-facing strings must be hiragana/katakana (target: elementary school age 1–3)
- `isNew: true` on a Block triggers yellow highlight arrow — always set it on newly added blocks in a step
- Block coordinates: x (east/right), y (south/depth into screen), z (up/height) — z=0 is ground level, z increases going straight up
- Never remove existing `id` fields from blocks — they are used for React keys
- Accent color `#FFD400` is reserved for LEGO-yellow UI elements
- Next.js version is 16 — check `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before using new APIs
- When adding a volume, update BOTH `volumes.ts` AND `generate-all-pdfs.mjs`

## Do Not

- Do not add English text to `label`, `howTo`, or `gridLabel` fields
- Do not change the isometric rendering logic in `MainBuildingStage.tsx` without understanding the SVG coordinate math
- Do not commit files under `lego-manual/output/` (PDFs/PNGs are generated artifacts)
